beer.beer_description:
Mountain Goat has been championing Aussie craft beer since 1997, putting our own spin on the
classics from our first ever release, Hightail Ale – a modern take on English Amber Ales, to the
original Summer Ale, and Steam Ale.
25 years on that innovative spirit has led us to our biggest challenge yet: reinvigorating a wheat
beer for a whole new generation of drinkers.
Made with locally-grown wheat, this beer isn’t just a riff on a classic; this is Aussie Wheat Beer.

APPEARANCE: Slight straw-like haze.

AROMA: Citrus from the Cascade hops.

FLAVOUR: Mandarin and pear.

TASTING NOTE: Soft citrus on the front palate from the hops, with a smooth, creamy body and a crisp finish that's immensely refreshing.

items.badge_description: Instead of a spot of tea, why not enjoy a proper pint. That doesn’t mean you can't get all dressed up for it, so throw on your fanciest hat and enjoy that brew!
One cannot live on dank hops alone. Tone down the bitterness and enjoy some smooth flavor. That's 40 different beers with an IBU of 20 or below. Try 5 more for Level 9!

Fresh from the tap is one of the best ways to enjoy a beer. Just try to use a glass and not drink directly from the tap, as tempting as it may be. That's 45 checkins with the serving style of Draft. Try 5 more for Level 10!

items.checkin_comment: Nice flavour. Light colour. Wheat not too overpowering.

items.checkin_comment:
The Aussie Wheat Beer. Clean with a crisp finish.
Smooth, with a lighter taste than the euro styles.
Tried this in the midst of South Aussie winter... Imagine this going down well during a spring summer sesh.
